Fixes:
error[E0425]: cannot find value `AT_EACCESS` in crate `libc`

If Android is presented with a call to `faccessat()` that
has a 4th argument that is any non-zero value, its `faccessat()`
will always return an error, so set the 4th argument to
0 instead of `AT_EACCESS` for the greatest chance of
somehow preventing this code from causing an error
at either build-time or runtime on Android.

https://cs.android.com/android/platform/superproject/+/android-16.0.0_r4:bionic/libc/bionic/faccessat.cpp;l=45

--- a/crates/fresh-editor/src/model/filesystem.rs
+++ b/crates/fresh-editor/src/model/filesystem.rs
@@ -1264,7 +1264,7 @@ impl StdFileSystem {
                 libc::AT_FDCWD,
                 c_path.as_ptr(),
                 libc::W_OK,
-                libc::AT_EACCESS,
+                0,
             )
         };
         Some(rc == 0)
